  "text": "We may now prove the posterior consistency theorem. From (4.3) onwards the proof is an adaptation of the proof of Theorem 2 of [CITATION_1] . We note that, the assumptions on limiting behaviour of measurement noise in [CITATION_2] are stronger: property (9) of [CITATION_3] is not assumed here for our J n . On the other hand a frequentist approach is used in [CITATION_4] , while here since J n is coming from a Bayesian approach, the norm in the regularisation term is stronger (it is related to the Cameron-Martin space of the Gaussian prior). That is why in our case asking what if u † is not in E and only in X, is relevant and is answered in Corollary 4.3 below.",
